### 📦 Conventional Commit Format

```text
<type>[optional scope]: <description>
```

#### ✅ Example
```text
feat(auth): add login functionality
fix(api): handle 500 error in user endpoint
docs(readme): update installation instructions
```

---

### 🔧 Common Types
| Type      | Purpose                                               |
|-----------|--------------------------------------------------------|
| `feat`    | A new feature                                          |
| `fix`     | A bug fix                                              |
| `docs`    | Documentation-only changes                            |
| `style`   | Changes that don't affect meaning (e.g., formatting)  |
| `refactor`| Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature |
| `test`    | Adding or modifying tests                             |
| `chore`   | Routine tasks like updates to build tools or dependencies |

---

### 🌱 Optional Scope
Use it to specify the area of the codebase affected:
```text
feat(cart): add item count display
```

---

### ⚙️ Why Use It?
- Clear commit history
- Easy integration with tools like semantic-release for automated versioning
- Consistency across teams

Here several examples of Conventional Commit messages tailored to common types of updates—you can tweak them based on your project or feature area:

---

### 🔧 Code Changes
```text
feat(login): add OAuth support for Google sign-in
fix(payment): resolve double-charge issue on checkout
refactor(profile): clean up state management logic
```

### 📚 Documentation
```text
docs(readme): update setup instructions for dev environment
docs(api): add usage examples for GET /users endpoint
```

### 🧪 Testing
```text
test(cart): add unit tests for item removal
test(auth): mock API calls for login flow tests
```

### 🎨 Styling and Layout
```text
style(header): align logo and navigation links
style(buttons): apply consistent padding and colors
```

### 🧹 Maintenance and Chores
```text
chore(deps): update react to v18.2.0
chore(ci): add GitHub Actions for lint and test
```

---
